53// Increment a number in a string.
54void increment(char* s) {
55 for (int i = static_cast<int>(std::strlen(s: s)) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
56 if (s[i] != '9') {
57 ++s[i];
58 break;
59 }
60 s[i] = '0';
61 }
62}
63
64TEST(util_test, increment) {
65 char s[10] = "123";
66 increment(s);
67 EXPECT_STREQ("124", s);
68 s[2] = '8';
69 increment(s);
70 EXPECT_STREQ("129", s);
71 increment(s);
72 EXPECT_STREQ("130", s);
73 s[1] = s[2] = '9';
74 increment(s);
75 EXPECT_STREQ("200", s);
76}

88TEST(util_test, utf8_to_utf16) {
89 auto u = fmt::detail::utf8_to_utf16("лошадка");
90 EXPECT_EQ(L"\x043B\x043E\x0448\x0430\x0434\x043A\x0430", u.str());
91 EXPECT_EQ(7, u.size());

93 EXPECT_EQ(L"\xD801\xDC37", fmt::detail::utf8_to_utf16("𐐷").str());
94 EXPECT_THROW_MSG(fmt::detail::utf8_to_utf16("\xc3\x28"), std::runtime_error,
95 "invalid utf8");
96 EXPECT_THROW_MSG(fmt::detail::utf8_to_utf16(fmt::string_view("л", 1)),
97 std::runtime_error, "invalid utf8");
98 EXPECT_EQ(L"123456", fmt::detail::utf8_to_utf16("123456").str());
99}

108TEST(util_test, allocator_ref) {
109 using test_allocator_ref = allocator_ref<mock_allocator<int>>;
110 auto check_forwarding = [](mock_allocator<int>& alloc,
111 test_allocator_ref& ref) {
112 int mem;
113 // Check if value_type is properly defined.
114 allocator_ref<mock_allocator<int>>::value_type* ptr = &mem;
115 // Check forwarding.
116 EXPECT_CALL(alloc, allocate(42)).WillOnce(action: Return(value: ptr));
117 ref.allocate(n: 42);
118 EXPECT_CALL(alloc, deallocate(ptr, 42));
119 ref.deallocate(p: ptr, n: 42);
120 };
121
122 StrictMock<mock_allocator<int>> alloc;
123 auto ref = test_allocator_ref(&alloc);
124 // Check if allocator_ref forwards to the underlying allocator.
125 check_forwarding(alloc, ref);
126 test_allocator_ref ref2(ref);
127 check_forwarding(alloc, ref2);
128 test_allocator_ref ref3;
129 EXPECT_EQ(nullptr, ref3.get());
130 ref3 = ref;
131 check_forwarding(alloc, ref3);
132}

134TEST(util_test, format_system_error) {
135 fmt::memory_buffer message;
136 fmt::format_system_error(out&: message, EDOM, message: "test");
137 auto ec = std::error_code(EDOM, std::generic_category());
138 EXPECT_EQ(to_string(message), std::system_error(ec, "test").what());
139 message = fmt::memory_buffer();
140
141 // Check if std::allocator throws on allocating max size_t / 2 chars.
142 size_t max_size = max_value<size_t>() / 2;
143 bool throws_on_alloc = false;
144 try {
145 auto alloc = std::allocator<char>();
146 alloc.deallocate(p: alloc.allocate(n: max_size), max_size);
147 } catch (const std::bad_alloc&) {
148 throws_on_alloc = true;
149 }
150 if (!throws_on_alloc) {
151 fmt::print(fmt: "warning: std::allocator allocates {} chars", args&: max_size);
152 return;
153 }
154}

190TEST(memory_buffer_test, move_ctor_inline_buffer) {
191 auto check_move_buffer =
192 [](const char* str, basic_memory_buffer<char, 5, std_allocator>& buffer) {
193 std::allocator<char>* alloc = buffer.get_allocator().get();
194 basic_memory_buffer<char, 5, std_allocator> buffer2(std::move(buffer));
195 // Move shouldn't destroy the inline content of the first buffer.
196 EXPECT_EQ(str, std::string(&buffer[0], buffer.size()));
197 EXPECT_EQ(str, std::string(&buffer2[0], buffer2.size()));
198 EXPECT_EQ(5u, buffer2.capacity());
199 // Move should transfer allocator.
200 EXPECT_EQ(nullptr, buffer.get_allocator().get());
201 EXPECT_EQ(alloc, buffer2.get_allocator().get());
202 };
203
204 auto alloc = std::allocator<char>();
205 basic_memory_buffer<char, 5, std_allocator> buffer((std_allocator(&alloc)));
206 const char test[] = "test";
207 buffer.append(range: string_view(test, 4));
208 check_move_buffer("test", buffer);
209 // Adding one more character fills the inline buffer, but doesn't cause
210 // dynamic allocation.
211 buffer.push_back(value: 'a');
212 check_move_buffer("testa", buffer);
213}

215TEST(memory_buffer_test, move_ctor_dynamic_buffer) {
216 auto alloc = std::allocator<char>();
217 basic_memory_buffer<char, 4, std_allocator> buffer((std_allocator(&alloc)));
218 const char test[] = "test";
219 buffer.append(begin: test, end: test + 4);
220 const char* inline_buffer_ptr = &buffer[0];
221 // Adding one more character causes the content to move from the inline to
222 // a dynamically allocated buffer.
223 buffer.push_back(value: 'a');
224 basic_memory_buffer<char, 4, std_allocator> buffer2(std::move(buffer));
225 // Move should rip the guts of the first buffer.
226 EXPECT_EQ(inline_buffer_ptr, &buffer[0]);
227 EXPECT_EQ("testa", std::string(&buffer2[0], buffer2.size()));
228 EXPECT_GT(buffer2.capacity(), 4u);
229}

262TEST(memory_buffer_test, grow) {
263 typedef allocator_ref<mock_allocator<int>> Allocator;
264 mock_allocator<int> alloc;
265 basic_memory_buffer<int, 10, Allocator> buffer((Allocator(&alloc)));
266 buffer.resize(count: 7);
267 using fmt::detail::to_unsigned;
268 for (int i = 0; i < 7; ++i) buffer[to_unsigned(value: i)] = i * i;
269 EXPECT_EQ(10u, buffer.capacity());
270 int mem[20];
271 mem[7] = 0xdead;
272 EXPECT_CALL(alloc, allocate(20)).WillOnce(action: Return(value: mem));
273 buffer.try_reserve(new_capacity: 20);
274 EXPECT_EQ(20u, buffer.capacity());
275 // Check if size elements have been copied
276 for (int i = 0; i < 7; ++i) EXPECT_EQ(i * i, buffer[to_unsigned(i)]);
277 // and no more than that.
278 EXPECT_EQ(0xdead, buffer[7]);
279 EXPECT_CALL(alloc, deallocate(mem, 20));
280}

299TEST(memory_buffer_test, exception_in_deallocate) {
300 using test_allocator = allocator_ref<mock_allocator<char>>;
301 StrictMock<mock_allocator<char>> alloc;
302 basic_memory_buffer<char, 10, test_allocator> buffer(
303 (test_allocator(&alloc)));
304 size_t size = 2 * fmt::inline_buffer_size;
305 auto mem = std::vector<char>(size);
306 {
307 EXPECT_CALL(alloc, allocate(size)).WillOnce(action: Return(value: &mem[0]));
308 buffer.resize(count: size);
309 std::fill(&buffer[0], &buffer[0] + size, 'x');
310 }
311 auto mem2 = std::vector<char>(2 * size);
312 {
313 EXPECT_CALL(alloc, allocate(2 * size)).WillOnce(action: Return(value: &mem2[0]));
314 auto e = std::exception();
315 EXPECT_CALL(alloc, deallocate(&mem[0], size)).WillOnce(action: testing::Throw(exception&: e));
316 EXPECT_THROW(buffer.reserve(2 * size), std::exception);
317 EXPECT_EQ(&mem2[0], &buffer[0]);
318 // Check that the data has been copied.
319 for (size_t i = 0; i < size; ++i) EXPECT_EQ('x', buffer[i]);
320 }
321 EXPECT_CALL(alloc, deallocate(&mem2[0], 2 * size));
322}

324template <typename Allocator, size_t MaxSize>
325class max_size_allocator : public Allocator {
326 public:
327 using typename Allocator::value_type;
328 size_t max_size() const FMT_NOEXCEPT { return MaxSize; }
329 value_type* allocate(size_t n) {
330 if (n > max_size()) {
331 throw std::length_error("size > max_size");
332 }
333 return std::allocator_traits<Allocator>::allocate(
334 *static_cast<Allocator*>(this), n);
335 }
336 void deallocate(value_type* p, size_t n) {
337 std::allocator_traits<Allocator>::deallocate(*static_cast<Allocator*>(this),
338 p, n);
339 }
340};

342TEST(memory_buffer_test, max_size_allocator) {
343 // 160 = 128 + 32
344 using test_allocator = max_size_allocator<std::allocator<char>, 160>;
345 basic_memory_buffer<char, 10, test_allocator> buffer;
346 buffer.resize(count: 128);
347 // new_capacity = 128 + 128/2 = 192 > 160
348 buffer.resize(count: 160); // Shouldn't throw.
349}

747TEST(format_test, runtime_width) {
748 char format_str[buffer_size];
749 safe_sprintf(buffer&: format_str, format: "{0:{%u", UINT_MAX);
750 increment(s: format_str + 4);
751 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime(format_str), 0), format_error,
752 "invalid format string");
753 size_t size = std::strlen(s: format_str);
754 format_str[size] = '}';
755 format_str[size + 1] = 0;
756 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime(format_str), 0), format_error,
757 "argument not found");
758 format_str[size + 1] = '}';
759 format_str[size + 2] = 0;
760 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime(format_str), 0), format_error,
761 "argument not found");
762
763 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:{"), 0), format_error,
764 "invalid format string");
765 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:{}"), 0), format_error,
766 "cannot switch from manual to automatic argument indexing");
767 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:{?}}"), 0), format_error,
768 "invalid format string");
769 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:{1}}"), 0), format_error,
770 "argument not found");
771
772 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:{0:}}"), 0), format_error,
773 "invalid format string");
774
775 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:{1}}"), 0, -1), format_error,
776 "negative width");
777 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:{1}}"), 0, (INT_MAX + 1u)),
778 format_error, "number is too big");
779 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:{1}}"), 0, -1l), format_error,
780 "negative width");
781 if (fmt::detail::const_check(value: sizeof(long) > sizeof(int))) {
782 long value = INT_MAX;
783 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:{1}}"), 0, (value + 1)),
784 format_error, "number is too big");
785 }
786 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:{1}}"), 0, (INT_MAX + 1ul)),
787 format_error, "number is too big");
788
789 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:{1}}"), 0, '0'), format_error,
790 "width is not integer");
791 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:{1}}"), 0, 0.0), format_error,
792 "width is not integer");
793
794 EXPECT_EQ(" -42", fmt::format("{0:{1}}", -42, 4));
795 EXPECT_EQ(" 42", fmt::format("{0:{1}}", 42u, 5));
796 EXPECT_EQ(" -42", fmt::format("{0:{1}}", -42l, 6));
797 EXPECT_EQ(" 42", fmt::format("{0:{1}}", 42ul, 7));
798 EXPECT_EQ(" -42", fmt::format("{0:{1}}", -42ll, 6));
799 EXPECT_EQ(" 42", fmt::format("{0:{1}}", 42ull, 7));
800 EXPECT_EQ(" -1.23", fmt::format("{0:{1}}", -1.23, 8));
801 EXPECT_EQ(" -1.23", fmt::format("{0:{1}}", -1.23l, 9));
802 EXPECT_EQ(" 0xcafe",
803 fmt::format("{0:{1}}", reinterpret_cast<void*>(0xcafe), 10));
804 EXPECT_EQ("x ", fmt::format("{0:{1}}", 'x', 11));
805 EXPECT_EQ("str ", fmt::format("{0:{1}}", "str", 12));
806}

962 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{}"), 0), format_error,
963 "cannot switch from manual to automatic argument indexing");
964 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{?}}"), 0), format_error,
965 "invalid format string");
966 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}"), 0, 0), format_error,
967 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
968 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}}"), 0), format_error,
969 "argument not found");
970
971 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{0:}}"), 0), format_error,
972 "invalid format string");
973
974 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}}"), 0, -1), format_error,
975 "negative precision");
976 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}}"), 0, (INT_MAX + 1u)),
977 format_error, "number is too big");
978 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}}"), 0, -1l), format_error,
979 "negative precision");
980 if (fmt::detail::const_check(value: sizeof(long) > sizeof(int))) {
981 long value = INT_MAX;
982 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}}"), 0, (value + 1)),
983 format_error, "number is too big");
984 }
985 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}}"), 0, (INT_MAX + 1ul)),
986 format_error, "number is too big");
987
988 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}}"), 0, '0'), format_error,
989 "precision is not integer");
990 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}}"), 0, 0.0), format_error,
991 "precision is not integer");
992
993 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}}"), 42, 2), format_error,
994 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
995 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}f}"), 42, 2), format_error,
996 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
997 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}}"), 42u, 2), format_error,
998 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
999 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}f}"), 42u, 2),
1000 format_error,
1001 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
1002 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}}"), 42l, 2), format_error,
1003 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
1004 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}f}"), 42l, 2),
1005 format_error,
1006 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
1007 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}}"), 42ul, 2),
1008 format_error,
1009 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
1010 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}f}"), 42ul, 2),
1011 format_error,
1012 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
1013 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}}"), 42ll, 2),
1014 format_error,
1015 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
1016 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}f}"), 42ll, 2),
1017 format_error,
1018 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
1019 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}}"), 42ull, 2),
1020 format_error,
1021 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
1022 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}f}"), 42ull, 2),
1023 format_error,
1024 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
1025 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:3.{1}}"), 'x', 0),
1026 format_error,
1027 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
1028 EXPECT_EQ("1.2", fmt::format("{0:.{1}}", 1.2345, 2));
1029 EXPECT_EQ("1.2", fmt::format("{1:.{0}}", 2, 1.2345l));
1030
1031 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}}"),
1032 reinterpret_cast<void*>(0xcafe), 2),
1033 format_error,
1034 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
1035 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:.{1}f}"),
1036 reinterpret_cast<void*>(0xcafe), 2),
1037 format_error,
1038 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
1039
1040 EXPECT_EQ("st", fmt::format("{0:.{1}}", "str", 2));

1060template <typename T>
1061void check_unknown_types(const T& value, const char* types, const char*) {
1062 char format_str[buffer_size];
1063 const char* special = ".0123456789L}";
1064 for (int i = CHAR_MIN; i <= CHAR_MAX; ++i) {
1065 char c = static_cast<char>(i);
1066 if (std::strchr(s: types, c: c) || std::strchr(s: special, c: c) || !c) continue;
1067 safe_sprintf(buffer&: format_str, format: "{0:10%c}", c);
1068 const char* message = "invalid type specifier";
1069 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime(format_str), value),
1070 format_error, message)
1071 << format_str << " " << message;
1072 }
1073}

1821 explicit variant(int) : type(int_type) {}
1822 explicit variant(const char*) : type(string_type) {}

1825FMT_BEGIN_NAMESPACE
1826template <> struct formatter<variant> : dynamic_formatter<> {
1827 auto format(variant value, format_context& ctx) -> decltype(ctx.out()) {
1828 if (value.type == variant::int_type)
1829 return dynamic_formatter<>::format(val: 42, ctx);
1830 return dynamic_formatter<>::format(val: "foo", ctx);
1831 }
1832};
1833FMT_END_NAMESPACE

1835TEST(format_test, dynamic_formatter) {
1836 auto num = variant(42);
1837 auto str = variant("foo");
1838 EXPECT_EQ("42", fmt::format("{:d}", num));
1839 EXPECT_EQ("foo", fmt::format("{:s}", str));
1840 EXPECT_EQ(" 42 foo ", fmt::format("{:{}} {:{}}", num, 3, str, 4));
1841 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{0:{}}"), num), format_error,
1842 "cannot switch from manual to automatic argument indexing");
1843 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{:{0}}"), num), format_error,
1844 "cannot switch from automatic to manual argument indexing");
1845 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{:+}"), str), format_error,
1846 "format specifier requires numeric argument");
1847 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{:-}"), str), format_error,
1848 "format specifier requires numeric argument");
1849 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{: }"), str), format_error,
1850 "format specifier requires numeric argument");
1851 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{:#}"), str), format_error,
1852 "format specifier requires numeric argument");
1853 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{:0}"), str), format_error,
1854 "format specifier requires numeric argument");
1855 EXPECT_THROW_MSG((void)fmt::format(runtime("{:.2}"), num), format_error,
1856 "precision not allowed for this argument type");
1857}

1945TEST(format_test, format_to_n) {

1971 result = fmt::format_to_n(out: buffer, n: 4, fmt: "{}", args: "ABCDE");
1972 EXPECT_EQ(5u, result.size);
1973 EXPECT_EQ("ABCD", fmt::string_view(buffer, 4));
1974
1975 buffer[3] = 'x';
1976 result = fmt::format_to_n(out: buffer, n: 3, fmt: "{}", args: std::string(1000, '*'));
1977 EXPECT_EQ(1000u, result.size);

2009struct test_error_handler {
2010 const char*& error;
2011
2012 FMT_CONSTEXPR test_error_handler(const char*& err) : error(err) {}
2013
2014 FMT_CONSTEXPR test_error_handler(const test_error_handler& other)
2015 : error(other.error) {}
2016
2017 FMT_CONSTEXPR void on_error(const char* message) {
2018 if (!error) error = message;
2019 }
2020};

2022FMT_CONSTEXPR size_t len(const char* s) {
2023 size_t len = 0;
2024 while (*s++) ++len;
2025 return len;
2026}
2027
2028FMT_CONSTEXPR bool equal(const char* s1, const char* s2) {
2029 if (!s1 || !s2) return s1 == s2;
2030 while (*s1 && *s1 == *s2) {
2031 ++s1;
2032 ++s2;
2033 }
2034 return *s1 == *s2;
2035}
2036
2037template <typename... Args>
2038FMT_CONSTEXPR bool test_error(const char* fmt, const char* expected_error) {
2039 const char* actual_error = nullptr;
2040 auto s = string_view(fmt, len(fmt));
2041 auto checker =
2042 fmt::detail::format_string_checker<char, test_error_handler, Args...>(
2043 s, test_error_handler(actual_error));
2044 fmt::detail::parse_format_string<true>(s, checker);
2045 return equal(actual_error, expected_error);
2046}
2047
2048# define EXPECT_ERROR_NOARGS(fmt, error) \
2049 static_assert(test_error(fmt, error), "")
2050# define EXPECT_ERROR(fmt, error, ...) \
2051 static_assert(test_error<__VA_ARGS__>(fmt, error), "")
